 is founded on a cultural revival that began in the 1950s and 60s but gained momentum from resistance to the outcome of the 1979 devolution referendum. That resistance, and the creative achievements which it generated, provoked a re-examination of the nation’s cultural history, revealing a wealth previously denied or forgotten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aArtxPolitical aspectszScotland. 0aCollective memoryzScotland. 0aNationalismzScotlandxHistory. 0aPolitics and literaturezScotlandxHistory. 0aPostcolonialismzScotland. 4aScottish Studies. 70(DE-588)4020517-40(DE-627)1063177680(DE-576)208933697aGeschichte2gnd 70(DE-588)4033542-20(DE-627)10625670X0(DE-576)20900259XaKulturelle Identität2gnd 70(DE-588)4041300-70(DE-627)1062197580(DE-576)209044373aNationalismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4046514-70(DE-627)1041522060(DE-576)209069945aPolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4071653-30(DE-627)1042886630(DE-576)209184574aGeistesgeschichte2gnd 70(DE-588)4121814-00(DE-627)1057668600(DE-576)209546395aUnabhängigkeitsbewegung2gnd 70(DE-588)4125698-00(DE-627)1044703480(DE-576)209578750aKultur2gnd 70(DE-588)4138031-90(DE-627)1056455750(DE-576)209682647aIdeengeschichte2gnd 7aHISTORY / Europe / Western.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311078043740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474435598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474435598/original  a978-3-11-078043-7  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK